                            <comment id="433967" author="pjones" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2024 14:44:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15259&quot; title=&quot;SLES15.2 sanity test_103a test_125 test_154a: setfacl: Option -m: Invalid argument near character 3&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15259&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-15259&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="417751" author="gerrit" created="Fri, 14 Jun 2024 08:05:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Li Xi &amp;lt;lixi@ddn.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/55430&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/55430&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17875&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_154b: FAIL: setfacl /mnt/lustre/.lustre/fid/[0x240004282:0x3:0x0] failed.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17875&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17875&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; test: skip 154b on SLES15&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: b2_15&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: ec89e93f932409f114aac6ab91623a14cf5933e5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="417748" author="lixi_wc" created="Fri, 14 Jun 2024 07:43:44 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;setfacl -R -m u:&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; can fail with the message &quot;setfacl: Option -m: Invalid argument near character 3&quot; if the user does not exists. Looks like b2_15 is missing patches that check whether the user exists:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15259&quot; title=&quot;SLES15.2 sanity test_103a test_125 test_154a: setfacl: Option -m: Invalid argument near character 3&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15259&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-15259&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: use existing usernames for setfacl&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16673&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_125: failures with aarch64 servers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16673&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16673&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: add checking for user USER0&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="417747" author="lixi_wc" created="Fri, 14 Jun 2024 07:31:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like setfacl quit on invalid argument before issuing any sys call to Lustre. And both failures found by Andreas were triggered on SLES 15.4. I am wondering whether the setfacl tool on SLES 15.4 treated the argument in a special way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="417745" author="lixi_wc" created="Fri, 14 Jun 2024 07:14:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On master branch:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;dot_lustre_fid_permission_check:
      setfacl -R -m u:$USER0:rwx $ffid || 
          error &quot;setfacl $ffid failed&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Codes on 2.15 are different here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Error log.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;setfacl: Option -m: Invalid argument near character 3
 sanity test_154b: @@@@@@ FAIL: setfacl /mnt/lustre/.lustre/fid/[0x240004282:0x3:0x0] failed. 
  Trace dump:
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6427:error()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity.sh:15250:dot_lustre_fid_permission_check()
